\title{meteoTidy: Quality Control, Correction, and Archiving of Meteorological Data}
\description{
Ingests meteorological observations and forecasts from multiple sources, applies quality control, gap-filling, and bias correction, and archives the results as a canonical, versioned Parquet store. Unlike general-purpose API clients such as 'weatherOz', 'meteoTidy' does not itself implement provider transports for every source; it wraps 'weatherOz' for 'SILO' access and layers curation, calibration, and a tidy read API on top of raw observations and forecasts from several providers.
